                     <interp inst="t18220911-290-person2624" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Lee. On the 12th of September, about seven o'clock in the evening, I was coming home, and saw the prisoner take a piece of print off the rail inside the shop; I got up to him when he was about four doors from the shop; he had it under his coat; I called, Stop thief! he ran and laid it on some tubs, but he was stopped before I lost sight of him; there were twenty-eight yards of it; I know it belongs to my master.</p>
